main event: A civilian reported seeing an explosion and finding pieces of dark material on the ground in St. Georges de Beauce, Quebec, Canada on June 16, 1964.
interesting points: The explosion occurred around 7:55 AM and the witness, a retired man, found the pieces of material after walking to the impact site around 4:50 PM.
The witness stated there was no displacement of soil or rocks, and no crater was found at the site.
Several pieces of dark, hardened material were collected and taken to the witness's home for inspection.
RCMP was notified and responded to the scene, but found no other evidence or witnesses.
The location of the object pieces is approximately 1.75 miles, 14 degrees, 30 seconds North, found between 10:30 PM and 11:00 PM on June 24, 1964.
location: St. Georges de Beauce, Quebec, Canada
photographs: yes, two photographs of cylindrical and elongated objects
